issue.title: Musikcube does not play songs from one album
issue.body:
Musikcube does not play songs from a specific album - when I try, it immediately says "playback is stopped". From the log file `~/.config/musikcube/log.txt`, the error is from ffmpegdecoder:
```
03:28:05 [info] [ffmpegdecoder] parsing data stream...
03:28:05 [error] [ffmpegdecoder] failed to find compatible audio stream
```
The album is "Chrono Trigger- Orchestral Selections Vol. I" (bought from Amazon). Interestingly, songs from Vol II play fine. Also, I can play the songs fine with `ffplay`. I don't know if this is a musikcube or ffmpeg issue.

I'm using Musikcube 0.96.6 #al7b9d91 (tried building from source also, issue persists), and on macOS Mojave.

comment.body:
> I'm using v0.99.5-1 as described above. I'm running an Arch-based distro called [endeavourOS](https://endeavouros.com/) and the package was installed through using `yay`. This is the one I have installed: https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/musikcube

Hitting the same error on [endeavourOS](https://endeavouros.com/)

issue.title: Won't open anymore

First off, thank you for supporting the project, It's really a great player!
Recently I re-installed my arch.
